ign:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0p=
x;">But by the time McCartney exited her partnership with Kering, in 2018, =
the concepts that
she innovated had overtaken her business. Activewear was quickly replacing =
denim as the general population=E2=80=99s everyday look=E2=80=94especially =
in the U.S.=E2=80=94and Adidas had prioritized higher-grossing partnerships=
, including one with <strong>Kanye West</strong>. Sustainability was everyo=
ne=E2=80=99s game. The Stella chain-link bag, which became popular with the=
 type of women who now carry Coach=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9CBrooklyn=E2=80=9D sho=
ulder boulder, receded in popularity.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom=
:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">At one point, McCartney=E2=80=99s s=
uiting was a uniform for women who followed corporate dress codes <em>and <=
/em>shopped on Net-a-Porter. These days, that=E2=80=99s a shrinking and emb=
attled population. Meanwhile, Kering=E2=80=99s business changed, too, becom=
ing hyper-focused on what were then the group=E2=80=99s fastest growing bra=
nds=E2=80=94including Saint Laurent, Gucci, and Balenciaga=E2=80=94as deals=
 with independent designers like McCartney, and later <strong>Christopher K=
ane</strong> and <strong>Joseph
Altuzarra</strong>, were unwound.</p></div>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
